yeah, it can look like RPC. however, zipcheck is a search resource, not a
method. and responses are cached.

while a single JS line is used, there are no async calls and XML is not
returned, in image is returned (not an image URI).

FWIW, there is another version that supports conneg for several media-types.
and a version that returns the query document if no data is passed in the
request.


